    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Biome: Oceans</em></p>\\n<p>Technically a symbiosis between a coral and an algae, Dratiddel is an incredibly rare organism found in deep-ocean trenches near volcanic vents. When harvested it remains viable for only 12 hours, even if kept in salt water, and then disintegrates. Shredded and mixed with holy oil, Dratiddel is used to brew a potent concoction known as Liquid Mortality.</p>\\n<p>When applied to a wound or ingested and successfully delivered, an undead creature subjected to this poison must make a DC 22 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the creature's Strength score is permanently reduced by 10. If this reduction drops an undead creature's Strength to 0, it is destroyed utterly and cannot be resurrected or reanimated except by a wish spell. A greater restoration spell (or similar magic) can restore the lost Strength.</p>",
